The paper deals with algorithmic techniques for solving the Rectilinear TSP and Rectilinear Steiner Tree problems, which are classic problems in computational geometry and optimization. The paper uses techniques from graph theory, parameterized complexity, and dynamic programming, which are common in the subfields of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
